cff-version: 1.2.0
title: >-
  Multi-agent reinforcement learning for relaxed
  probability updating games
message: >-
  If you use this software, please cite it using the
  metadata from this file.
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Collin
    family-names: Aldaibis
repository-code: >-
  https://github.com/caldaibis/probability-updating-games-marl
abstract: >-
  Implementation accompanying the master thesis
  "Investigating relaxed probability updating games".
  It models general-sum probability updating games,
  exposes them as OpenAI Gym-like environments, and uses
  Ray Tune and Ray RLlib (PPO and other policy gradient
  methods) to learn optimal strategies for both the host
  and the contestant, empirically converging to Nash
  equilibria.
keywords:
  - multi-agent reinforcement learning
  - probability updating games
  - Nash equilibrium
  - PPO
  - Ray RLlib
license: MIT
